# Local preview (Cursor Browser)

When the user asks to **open preview**, **open the app**, or load **localhost** **inside Cursor**, treat **Cursor’s built-in Agent Browser** as the primary target (inline pane or browser window, `@browser` / browser MCP tools per [Cursor Browser docs](https://cursor.com/docs/agent/browser)).

## Do

- Prefer **`@browser`** (Agent) with an explicit URL after a dev or preview server is running.
- Use **`http://localhost:5173/`** when they use **`bun run dev`** (Vite dev server).
- Use **`http://localhost:4173/`** when they use **`bun run preview`** (Vite production preview).

## Avoid as the only answer

- Do not rely solely on **`Start-Process`** / the **system default browser** when they asked for preview **in Cursor**.

## If this chat has no browser tools

- Say clearly that **Agent + `@browser`** (with approval for navigate) opens the built-in pane, and give the exact URL and which script to run first.

## Optional fallback

- Workspace task **“Open in Simple Browser (…)”** in `.vscode/tasks.json` is a VS Code–style fallback only if the user wants the Simple Browser instead.
